olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
20 g plant-based butter
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet Chilli & Lime Jackfruit
¼ tsp salt
2 Plant-Based Burger Buns
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
2 clove garlic

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries. Place on a
lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Spread
out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• While the fries are baking, finely chop garlic. Grate carrot.

• When the fries have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan
over medium-high heat. Heat the plant-based butter and a drizzle of
olive oil.
• Cook 1/2 the carrot until tender, 3-4 minutes. Add garlic and sweet soy
seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add chilli & lime jackfruit and the salt, stirring, until heated through,
2-3 minutes.
• Meanwhile, slice plant-based burger buns in half and bake directly on a
wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.

• In a large bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, remaining carrot, a pinch
of salt and a drizzle of olive oil and white wine vinegar.
• Spread each bun with plant-based mayo, then top with chilli and lime
jackfruit and slaw.
• Serve with fries and any remaining slaw.